  Bugs (functional correctness)

  1. block_device_path_from_lun_rec — multipath path overwritten (Common.pm:1867)

  This is the most impactful bug. When multipath is enabled and the volume is already staged ($lunrec->{multipath} = 1), the function:
  - Correctly computes $block_device_path = block_device_path_from_serial($id, 1) → /dev/mapper/…
  - Then falls through to the unconditional block below the if (get_multipath) scope
  - Which overwrites it: $block_device_path = block_device_path_from_serial($id, 0) → /dev/disk/by-id/scsi-…
  - Returns the wrong, non-multipath path

  if ( get_multipath($ctx) ) {
      unless ($lunrec->{multipath}) {
          ...
          return $block_dev;    # ← early return only on first-time staging
      }
      $block_device_path = block_device_path_from_serial( $id, 1 );
      # ← no return here; falls through
  }

  # This ALWAYS runs and overwrites the multipath path:
  $block_device_path = block_device_path_from_serial( $id, 0 );
  return $block_device_path;   # always /dev/disk/by-id/... even with multipath

  Fix: add return $block_device_path; inside the if (get_multipath) block, after setting it.

  ---
  2. volume_unstage_iscsi_device — basename called on potentially undef $bdp (Common.pm:2197)

  my $bdp;
  if ( $idp =~ /^([\:\-\@\w.\/]+)$/ ) {
      my $cmd = [ "readlink", "-f", $1 ];
      run_command( $cmd, outfunc => sub {
          if ( $path =~ /^([\:\-\@\w.\/]+)$/ ) { $bdp = $1; }  # only set if matches
          ...
      }, ... );
  }
  my $block_device_name = File::Basename::basename($bdp);  # $bdp still undef if readlink failed

  If readlink -f produces output that doesn't match the safe-word regex, $bdp remains undef. basename(undef) in File::Basename returns "." on some perls or warns/dies on others. The subsequent regex unless ($block_device_name =~ /^[a-z0-9]+$/) then fails with a misleading error.

  ---
  3. lun_record_local_delete — opendir without error check (Common.pm:2933)

  if ( rmdir( $ltldir ) ) {
      my $dh;
      opendir( $dh, $ltdir );                          # ← no 'or die'
      my @entries = grep { $_ ne '.' && $_ ne '..' } readdir $dh;
      closedir $dh;
      unless ( @entries ) {
          volume_unstage_iscsi( $ctx, $targetname );   # ← called if opendir silently fails
          ...
      }
  }

  If opendir fails (permissions, race condition), readdir returns undef, @entries is empty, and volume_unstage_iscsi is called prematurely — logging out the iSCSI session while other LUNs on that target may still be active.

  ---
  4. safe_ford — exported but not defined (Common.pm:51)

  our @EXPORT_OK = qw(
    ...
    safe_ford       # ← no sub safe_ford exists anywhere
    ...
  );

  Any caller that use OpenEJovianDSS::Common qw(safe_ford) will get "Undefined subroutine" at runtime. Should be removed from @EXPORT_OK.

  ---
  5. get_control_addresses — length check rejects valid short addresses (Common.pm:279)

  if ( length( $scfg->{control_addresses} ) > 4 ) {

  IPv6 loopback ::1 is 3 characters — rejected. This silently falls back to data_addresses. Should be > 0.

  ---
  6. vm_tag_force_rollback_is_set — potential whitespace in tag comparison (Common.pm:3532)

  my @tags = split(/[,;]/, $conf->{tags});
  foreach my $tag (@tags) {
      if ($tag eq 'force_rollback') {   # ← no trim

  If Proxmox stores tags as "snap1; force_rollback", splitting on ; yields " force_rollback" with a leading space. The eq comparison fails silently, making the tag invisible. Each tag needs $tag =~ s/^\s+|\s+$//g before comparison.

  ---
  Design issues

  7. Multi-cluster naming conflict — hardcoded target group names

  As detailed in the previous analysis: get_vm_target_group_name returns "vm-${vmid}" and get_content_target_group_name returns "proxmox-content" — both hardcoded. Two clusters sharing one JovianDSS pool will fight over the same JovianDSS-side target group objects. Neither function receives $storeid or any cluster-distinguishing input even though that information is available in $ctx.

  ---
  8. ha_state_is_defined + ha_state_get — two pvesh calls for one dataset (Common.pm:1964, 2007)

  volume_rollback_is_possible calls ha_state_is_defined first, then if that returns true, calls ha_state_get. Both spawn pvesh get /cluster/ha/resources/<vmid> — the same REST call twice in sequence. ha_state_is_defined should return the decoded JSON hash, not just a boolean, so the caller can extract state from it without a second round-trip.

  ---
  9. joviandss_cmd — $err accumulates across retries (Common.pm:751)

  my $err = undef;
  while ( $retry_count <= $retries ) {
      ...
      if ( $rerr && $rerr =~ /got timeout/ ) {
          $retry_count++;
          $msg = '';
          $err = undef;    # ← reset

  $err IS reset on timeout retry. But this code only resets on got timeout, not on exitcode != 0. If jdssc exits non-zero on attempt 1, $err is set, and the loop breaks with die "${err}\n". The retry path works correctly for timeouts. Minor: $err is reset to undef not '' while $msg is reset to '' — inconsistency, but harmless.

  ---
  10. lun_record_update_device — up to 20 seconds of sleep per call (Common.pm:3289)

  The retry loop runs up to 10 iterations, with sleep(1) near the top AND sleep(1) at the bottom of each iteration (lines 3400 and 3434). That is a potential 20-second stall during volume activation and resize. Given this is called inside the per-VM lock's 60-second alarm window, it consumes a third of the available window.

  ---
  Code quality

  11. store_settup — typo in function name (Common.pm:3484)

  Should be store_setup. Minor, but it's a public export used in Plugin.pm's activate_storage.

  ---
  12. sleep(3) before dying on multiple LUN records (Plugin.pm:392)

  sleep(3);
  die "Resource ${volname} have multiple records:\n${records_info}";

  Debugging artifact — adds 3 seconds of latency before every "multiple records" error, which is already an error path. Remove.

  ---
  13. ha_state_is_defined — leading whitespace in sub (Common.pm:1964)

  sub ha_state_is_defined {
       my ($ctx, $vmid) = @_;   # ← 5-space indent instead of 4

  Minor style inconsistency.

  ---
